text: Loktevsky District () is an administrativeLaw #28-ZS and municipalLaw #86-ZS district (raion), one of the fifty-nine in Altai Krai, Russia. It is located in the southwest of the krai. The area of the district is . Its administrative center is the town of Gornyak. Population: The population of Gornyak accounts for 46.9% of the district's total population. ==References== ===Notes=== ===Sources=== * * Category:Districts of Altai Krai
